primary.context: Customer has never logged in before and needs access
primary.detail: The agent verified the caller and sent a Clubhouse registration link to the customer's updated email address.

steps: Customer requested help logging into their account.
Agent performed account lookup and identity verification.
Agent identified that the customer needed a new registration link.
Agent confirmed contact information and updated the email address for delivery.
Agent sent the Clubhouse registration link and confirmed completion.

clarifications.note: Agent confirmed if registration link was needed

corrections.note: Customer corrected outdated email and phone digit

actions.detail: Located record using phone number provided
Verified name and state of residence

insights.summary: The customer wanted to access their owner account for the first time. The agent successfully verified the account, updated the email address on file, and sent a Clubhouse registration link.
